remarks: Two equivalent expressions for double existential uniqueness.  Curiously, we can put ` E! ` on either of the internal conjuncts but not both.  We can also commute ` E! x E! y ` using ~ 2eu7 .  (Contributed by NM, 20-Feb-2005.)
statement: 2eu8 $p |- ( E! x E! y ( E. x ph /\ E. y ph ) <-> E! x E! y ( E! x ph /\ E. y ph ) ) $.
